{"type": "root", "attrs": {}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Loops and flow control"], "extent": [0, 27]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["See also ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/vex/functions/", "type": "link", "text": ["VEX functions"], "fullpath": "/vex/functions/index"}, ". Most of the work in VEX is done with function calls. Most of the statements are looping constructs, many of which may be familiar from other languages such as C. While ", {"type": "code", "text": ["print"]}, " is a statement in some languages (such as Python), in VEX you print using ", {"scheme": "Vex", "value": "/vex/functions/printf", "type": "link", "text": ["the printf function"], "fallback_text": "printf()", "fullpath": "/vex/functions/printf"}, "."], "extent": [27, 356]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["{}"], "extent": [356, 365], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["As in C and many other languages, you can enclose multiple statements inside curly braces to act as a block."], "extent": [365, 476]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["For example, the ", {"type": "code", "text": ["if"]}, " statement can execute one statement:"], "extent": [476, 536]}, {"lang": "vex", "type": "pre", "indent": 0, "text": ["\nif ( needs_zapping() ) zap()\n"], "extent": [536, 579]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["\u2026or a block inside curly braces:"], "extent": [579, 620]}, {"lang": "vex", "type": "pre", "indent": 0, "text": ["\nif ( needs_zapping() ) {\n    zap()\n    disintegrate()\n    remove_dust()\n}\n"], "extent": [620, 708]}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["do loop"], "extent": [708, 724], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": [{"type": "code", "text": ["do ", {"type": "var", "text": ["statement"]}, " [while (", {"type": "var", "text": ["condition"]}, ")]"]}], "extent": [724, 769]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["Executes ", {"type": "var", "text": ["statement"]}, ", and then loops if ", {"type": "var", "text": ["condition"]}, " is true. Unlike ", {"type": "code", "text": ["while"]}, ", ", {"type": "code", "text": ["do"]}, " is guaranteed to execute the ", {"type": "var", "text": ["statement"]}, " at least once."], "extent": [769, 915]}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["for loop"], "extent": [915, 930], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": [{"type": "code", "text": ["for (", {"type": "var", "text": ["init"]}, "; ", {"type": "var", "text": ["condition"]}, "; ", {"type": "var", "text": ["change"]}, ") ", {"type": "var", "text": ["statement"]}]}], "extent": [930, 990]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["Standard C-style ", {"type": "code", "text": ["for"]}, " loop. Performs the ", {"type": "var", "text": ["init"]}, " statement, then executes ", {"type": "var", "text": ["statement"]}, " repeatedly while ", {"type": "var", "text": ["condition"]}, " is true, executing the ", {"type": "var", "text": ["change"]}, " statement at the end of each iteration."], "extent": [990, 1187]}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["foreach loop"], "extent": [1187, 1206], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": [{"type": "code", "text": ["foreach (", {"type": "var", "text": ["value"]}, "; ", {"type": "var", "text": ["array"]}, ") ", {"type": "var", "text": ["statement"]}]}], "extent": [1206, 1255]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": [{"type": "code", "text": ["foreach (", {"type": "var", "text": ["index"]}, ", ", {"type": "var", "text": ["value"]}, "; ", {"type": "var", "text": ["array"]}, ") ", {"type": "var", "text": ["statement"]}]}], "extent": [1255, 1314]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["Executes ", {"type": "var", "text": ["statement"]}, " for each member of ", {"type": "var", "text": ["array"]}, " (optionally sets\n", {"type": "var", "text": ["index"]}, " to the current position in the array). See ", {"scheme": "Vex", "value": "/vex/functions/foreach", "type": "link", "text": "", "fallback_text": "foreach()", "fullpath": "/vex/functions/foreach"}, "."], "extent": [1314, 1453]}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["while loop"], "extent": [1453, 1470], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": [{"type": "code", "text": ["while (", {"type": "var", "text": ["condition"]}, ") ", {"type": "var", "text": ["statement"]}]}], "extent": [1470, 1510]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["Executes ", {"type": "var", "text": ["statement"]}, " repeatedly while ", {"type": "var", "text": ["condition"]}, " is true."], "extent": [1510, 1575]}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Other looping statements"], "extent": [1575, 1606], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["The ", {"scheme": "Vex", "value": "/vex/functions/forpoints", "type": "link", "text": "", "fallback_text": "forpoints()", "fullpath": "/vex/functions/forpoints"}, ", ", {"scheme": "Vex", "value": "/vex/functions/illuminance", "type": "link", "text": "", "fallback_text": "illuminance()", "fullpath": "/vex/functions/illuminance"}, ", and ", {"scheme": "Vex", "value": "/vex/functions/gather", "type": "link", "text": "", "fallback_text": "gather()", "fullpath": "/vex/functions/gather"}, " statements let you loop over data being processed by VEX."], "extent": [1606, 1724]}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["if"], "extent": [1724, 1733], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": [{"type": "code", "text": ["if (", {"type": "var", "text": ["condition"]}, ") ", {"type": "var", "text": ["statement_if_true"]}, " [else ", {"type": "var", "text": ["statement_if_false"]}, "]"]}], "extent": [1733, 1808]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["Executes ", {"type": "var", "text": ["statement_if_true"]}, " if ", {"type": "var", "text": ["condition"]}, " is true."], "extent": [1808, 1866]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["If the ", {"type": "code", "text": ["else"]}, " clause is included, ", {"type": "var", "text": ["statement_if_false"]}, " is executed if ", {"type": "var", "text": ["condition"]}, " is false."], "extent": [1866, 1964]}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["return"], "extent": [1964, 1977], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["Exits the function with an optional return value."], "extent": [1977, 2029]}, {"lang": "vex", "type": "pre", "indent": 0, "text": ["\nint max(int a, b) {\n    if (a > b) {\n        return a;\n    }\n    return b;\n}\n"], "extent": [2029, 2120]}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["break"], "extent": [2120, 2134], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": [{"type": "code", "text": ["break"]}, " immediately exits the loop. It is useful with the ", {"type": "code", "text": ["if"]}, " statement to stop looping early when some condition is reached."], "extent": [2134, 2263]}, {"lang": "vex", "type": "pre", "indent": 0, "text": ["\nfor (int i = 0; i < sizes; i++)\n{\n    mixamount += getAmount(roughness);\n    if (mixamount > 1) {\n        break;\n    }\n}\n"], "extent": [2263, 2398]}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["continue"], "extent": [2398, 2415], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": [{"type": "code", "text": ["continue"]}, " jumps immediately to the next iteration of the loop."], "extent": [2415, 2481]}, {"lang": "vex", "type": "pre", "indent": 0, "text": ["\nforeach (x; myarray) {\n    if (x < 10) continue;\n    ...\n}\n"], "extent": [2481, 2554]}]}], "title": ["Loops and flow control"]}